âœ… Sample Program 2: Display Multiple Users
ðŸ”¹ Code:
html
Copy
Edit
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Multiple Users - JSON Example</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>User List</h1>
  <div id="userList"></div>

  <script>
    // JSON array as a string
    const jsonString = `[
      {"name": "Alice", "age": 28, "email": "alice@example.com"},
      {"name": "Bob", "age": 34, "email": "bob@example.com"},
      {"name": "Charlie", "age": 22, "email": "charlie@example.com"}
    ]`;

    // Parse JSON string into JavaScript array
    const users = JSON.parse(jsonString);

    // Get the target div
    const container = document.getElementById("userList");

    // Build HTML content
    users.forEach(user => {
      const userHTML = `
        <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
          <strong>Name:</strong> ${user.name}<br>
          <strong>Age:</strong> ${user.age}<br>
          <strong>Email:</strong> ${user.email}
        </div>
      `;
      container.innerHTML += userHTML;
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
ðŸ’¾ How to Save and Run
âœ… Step 1: Save the File
Open Notepad or any text/code editor.

Paste the code above.

Save it as: users.html

âœ… Step 2: Run It
Double-click the users.html file to open it in your browser.

Youâ€™ll see the list of users with their name, age, and email displayed.

